article.headline: Florida Gulf Coast 50, North Florida 44
article.story: FORT MYERS, Fla. -- Derrick O'Neil scored on a go-ahead layup with 1 minute left in the game to help Florida Gulf Coast beat North Florida 50-44 on Friday night. The Eagles (9-12, 5-5 in Atlantic Sun Conference) trailed 26-15 at halftime after making only five field goals and shooting 25 percent from the floor in the first half. But Florida Gulf Coast shot 50 percent after the break, outscoring North Florida 35-18 onto the victory. O'Neil, who scored 10 of his 11 points in the second half, also led Florida Gulf Coast with eight rebounds. He gave the Eagles their first lead of the game at 33-32 on two free throws with 10 minutes left in the second half. Reggie Chambers scored 11 points for Florida Gulf Coast. Eni Cuka and Stan Januska each scored 10 points each for North Florida (3-16, 1-8).
